## Recommended Launch Strategy

### Option 1: MVP Launch (4-6 weeks)
**Ship v1.0 with core features only**

Include:
- ✅ Home, Search, Recipe Detail
- ✅ Ingredients, Equipment, Cooking Mode
- ✅ Tools (timer, converter, calculator)
- ✅ Shopping list
- ✅ Bilingual support

Defer:
- ❌ User accounts/cloud sync
- ❌ Advanced recipe builder
- ❌ Lab notes in UI
- ❌ AI step images

**Pros:** Faster launch, simpler code, fewer bugs  
**Cons:** Limited features, can't sync data

### Option 2: Extended Launch (8-10 weeks)
**Ship v1.0 with more features**

Add to MVP:
- User accounts (simple email auth)
- Cloud sync for favorites/shopping list
- Advanced recipe builder (with bug fix)
- Lab notes in Cooking Mode

**Pros:** More features, better UX  
**Cons:** More work, higher risk of bugs

### Recommendation: **OPTION 1 (MVP)**
- Faster to market (6 weeks vs 10 weeks)
- Lower risk (fewer untested features)
- Can add v1.1 features based on user feedback
- Simpler to maintain and debug

